            <title><![CDATA[Note 2: Learning Git]]></title>
            <link>https://ivanignatiev.github.io/learning-git</link>
            <guid>https://ivanignatiev.github.io/learning-git</guid>
            <pubDate>Thu, 23 Jan 2025 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Git is the foundation of collaboration within any coding team today. It’s a fundamental technical skill that can cause a daily pain if not mastered.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Git is the foundation of collaboration within any coding team today. It’s a fundamental technical skill that can cause a daily pain if not mastered.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="basics">Basics<a href="https://ivanignatiev.github.io/learning-git#basics" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Basics" title="Direct link to Basics">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li>Book: <a href="https://learning.oreilly.com/library/view/learning-git/9781098133900/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">O'Reilly - Anna Skoulikari - Learning Git</a></li>
<li>Visual Tool: <a href="https://learngitbranching.js.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Learn Git Branching</a></li>
<li><a href="https://gitimmersion.com/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Git Immersion</a></li>
<li><a href="https://gitbybit.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitByBit</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="advanced">Advanced<a href="https://ivanignatiev.github.io/learning-git#advanced" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Advanced" title="Direct link to Advanced">​</a></h2>
<p>Everything which will help to apply this tool in the real world practice and establish a good style shared across all project contributors.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://ooloo.io/project/github-flow/mindset" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ooloo.io github flow course</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Conventional Commits</a></li>
<li><a href="https://nvie.com/posts/a-successful-git-branching-model/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Git flow</a></li>
<li>Best Practices for Git:<!-- -->
<ul>
<li><a href="https://about.gitlab.com/topics/version-control/version-control-best-practices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://about.gitlab.com/topics/version-control/version-control-best-practices/</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Best Practices for GitHub:<!-- -->
<ul>
<li><a href="https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/creating-and-managing-repositories/best-practices-for-repositories" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/creating-and-managing-repositories/best-practices-for-repositories</a></li>
<li><a href="https://dev.to/pwd9000/github-repository-best-practices-23ck" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://dev.to/pwd9000/github-repository-best-practices-23ck</a></li>
<li><a href="https://medium.com/datreeio/top-10-github-best-practices-for-developers-d6309a613227" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://medium.com/datreeio/top-10-github-best-practices-for-developers-d6309a613227</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Best Practices for Azure Repos (Azure DevOps):<!-- -->
<ul>
<li><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/devops/repos/git/git-branching-guidance?view=azure-devops" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/devops/repos/git/git-branching-guidance?view=azure-devops</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="transversal-resources">Transversal Resources<a href="https://ivanignatiev.github.io/learning-git#transversal-resources" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Transversal Resources" title="Direct link to Transversal Resources">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://roadmap.sh/git-github" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Learn Git and GitHub roadmap</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome?tab=readme-ov-file#development-environment" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Git recourses from awesome repository</a></li>
<li>Free eBook: <a href="https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Pro Git</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="tools">Tools<a href="https://ivanignatiev.github.io/learning-git#tools" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Tools" title="Direct link to Tools">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/apps/desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Desktop</a></li>
<li><a href="https://gitbutler.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitButler</a></li>
</ul>]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Note 1: Visual Communication Tools for Architecture]]></title>
            <link>https://ivanignatiev.github.io/visual-communication-tools-for-architecture</link>
            <guid>https://ivanignatiev.github.io/visual-communication-tools-for-architecture</guid>
            <pubDate>Tue, 21 Jan 2025 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[This article focuses on visual tools to represent IT architectures and resources for those tools.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This article focuses on visual tools to represent IT architectures and resources for those tools.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="what-i-use">What I use<a href="https://ivanignatiev.github.io/visual-communication-tools-for-architecture#what-i-use" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to What I use" title="Direct link to What I use">​</a></h2>
<p>Tools for Ad-hoc communication, drafting, and wireframing:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://excalidraw.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://excalidraw.com/</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.figma.com/figjam/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.figma.com/figjam/</a></li>
<li><a href="https://miro.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://miro.com/</a></li>
<li><a href="https://xmind.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://xmind.app/</a> (MindMaps)</li>
</ul>
<p>Tools to transform drafts to more presentable assets:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://draw.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">draw.io</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/visio/flowchart-software" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Microsoft Visio</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Tools for use in documentation (Diagrams as a Code):</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.mermaidchart.com/play" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mermaid Playground</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="what-i-use-as-an-azure-consultant">What I use, As an Azure Consultant:<a href="https://ivanignatiev.github.io/visual-communication-tools-for-architecture#what-i-use-as-an-azure-consultant" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to What I use, As an Azure Consultant:" title="Direct link to What I use, As an Azure Consultant:">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li>In Enterprise world many documentation is done with <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/visio/flowchart-software" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Microsoft Visio</a></li>
<li>Azure Services Icons from <a href="https://github.com/David-Summers/Azure-Design" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Azure-Design repository</a></li>
<li><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/architecture/icons/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Official Azure Icons from Microsoft</a></li>
<li>Visio files could be found in architectures from <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/architecture/browse/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Azure Architecture Center</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="other">Other<a href="https://ivanignatiev.github.io/visual-communication-tools-for-architecture#other" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Other" title="Direct link to Other">​</a></h2>
<p>To make visual communication clear we need to decide on style and configure out tools:</p>
<ul>
<li>Color scheme</li>
<li>Rounding</li>
<li>Fonts</li>
</ul>
<p>That is why it is import to look around, analyze, and compare. When you look to graphic designer, photographer courses you you always find a section about "collecting inspirations", "observation and others work observation", "designer eye training".</p>
<p>Here I like to maintain my collection for observability:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/simskij/awesome-software-architecture?tab=readme-ov-file#tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tools section in Awesome Software Architecture</a></li>
<li><a href="https://pbea.iankoenig.com/visio.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Principal Based Enterprise Architecture (PBEA) stencils</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.archimatetool.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Archi - Archimate Tool</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.eraser.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Eraser</a></li>
<li><a href="https://plantuml.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PlantUML</a></li>
<li><a href="https://d2lang.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">D2</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.ilograph.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ilograph</a></li>
<li><a href="https://c4model.com/tooling" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">C4 Model - Tooling</a></li>
</ul>]]></content:encoded>
